  Terms of Service for Stygian-Relay

  Last Updated: November 10, 2025

  1. Acceptance of Terms
  By adding or using Stygian-Relay ("the Bot") in your Discord server, you are agreeing to be bound by these
  Terms of Service ("ToS"). If you do not agree with these terms, you must not use the Bot and should remove
  it from your server.

  2. Description of Service
  The Bot is designed to provide message forwarding and relay capabilities between channels and servers ("the
  Service"). Its features are provided as-is and are subject to change, modification, or discontinuation at
  any time, with or without notice. As the Bot is in active development, features may change frequently.

  3. User Responsibilities
   - You must have the necessary permissions to add a bot to any server where you install it.
   - You are responsible for the configuration of the Bot in your server, including the forwarding rules you
     create.
   - You agree not to use the Service for any purpose that is illegal, malicious, or violates Discord's Terms of
     Service. This includes, but is not limited to, spamming, harassment, or distributing harmful content.
   - Misuse of the Service may result in a temporary or permanent ban of your server and its users from
     accessing the Bot.

  4. Termination
  We reserve the right to terminate or restrict access to the Service for any server or user who violates
  these ToS, without notice or liability.

  5. Disclaimer of Warranties
  The Service is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no warranty that the Service will be
  uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error-free.

  6. Limitation of Liability
  In no event shall the developers of Stygian-Relay be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special,
  or consequential damages resulting from the use or the inability to use the Service.

